cpputest
------------------------------------------
CppUTest is a C /C++ based unit xUnit test framework for unit testing and for
test-driving your code. It is written in C++ but is used in C and C++ projects
and frequently used in embedded systems but it works for any C/C++ project.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libCppUTest-devel-4.0-1bl2
  libCppUTest4-4.0-1bl2
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/cpputest/cpputest

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/cpputest/cpputest/archive/refs/tags/v4.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cpputest-4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cpputest-4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cpputest-4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cpputest-4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libCppUTest4-4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libCppUTest-devel-4.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

